# Just need a distro?
</div>
<div class="right" markdown="1">
You can either download the latest [snapshot](http://jmstester.fusesource.org/repo/snapshot) or a [released version](http://jmstester.fusesource.org/repo/release) of *{project_name:}* from our maven repositories.
</div>

<div class="left" markdown="1">
# Are you a Maven User?
</div>
<div class="right" markdown="1">
Just add the following to your *pom.xml*
</div> 
<div class="right">
{coderay:: xml}<dependency>
  <groupId>org.fusesource.{project_id:}</groupId>
  <artifactId>{project_id:}-core</artifactId>
  <version>${{project_id:}-version}</version>  
</dependency>
{coderay}
</div>
<div class="right" markdown="1">
You should ensure you have the fusesource.com Maven repository defined in your *pom.xml*</div> 
<div class="right">
{coderay:: xml}  <repositories>
   <repository>
     <id>jmstester.release</id>
     <name>FuseSource Community {project_name:} Repository</name>
     <url>http://jmstester.fusesource.org/repo/release</url>
     <snapshots>
       <enabled>false</enabled>
     </snapshots>
     <releases>
       <enabled>true</enabled>
     </releases>
   </repository>
   <repository>
     <id>jmstester.snapshot</id>
     <name>FuseSource Community {project_name:} snapshot Repository</name>
     <url>http://jmstester.fusesource.org/repo/snapshot</url>
     <snapshots>
       <enabled>true</enabled>
     </snapshots>
     <releases>
       <enabled>false</enabled>
     </releases>
   </repository>
 </repositories>
{coderay}
</div>


